attributes.documentation:
@title Initializable
 * @dev Helper contract to support initializer functions. To use it, replace
the constructor with a function that has the `initializer` modifier.
WARNING: Unlike constructors, initializer functions must be manually
invoked. This applies both to deploying an Initializable contract, as well
as extending an Initializable contract via inheritance.
WARNING: When used with inheritance, manual care must be taken to not invoke
a parent initializer twice, or ensure that all initializers are idempotent,
because this is not dealt with automatically as with constructors.
attributes.name: Initializable

attributes.documentation: @dev Modifier to use in the initializer function of a contract.
attributes.name: initializer

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "Contract instance has already been initialized"

attributes.type: literal_string "Contract instance has already been initialized"
attributes.value: Contract instance has already been initialized

attributes.documentation: @dev Returns true if and only if the function is running in the constructor
attributes.name: isConstructor

attributes.documentation:
@dev Contract module which provides a basic access control mechanism, where
there is an account (an owner) that can be granted exclusive access to
specific functions.
 * By default, the owner account will be the one that deploys the contract. This
can later be changed with {transferOwnership}.
 * This module is used through inheritance. It will make available the modifier
`onlyOwner`, which can be applied to your functions to restrict their use to
the owner.
attributes.name: OwnableUpgradeSafe

attributes.documentation: @dev Initializes the contract setting the deployer as the initial owner.
attributes.name: __Ownable_init

attributes.documentation: @dev Returns the address of the current owner.
attributes.name: owner

attributes.documentation: @dev Throws if called by any account other than the owner.
attributes.name: onlyOwner

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "Ownable: caller is not the owner"

attributes.type: literal_string "Ownable: caller is not the owner"
attributes.value: Ownable: caller is not the owner

attributes.documentation:
@dev Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call
`onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner.
     * NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner,
thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.
attributes.name: renounceOwnership

attributes.documentation:
@dev Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`).
Can only be called by the current owner.
attributes.name: transferOwnership

argumentTypes.typeString: literal_string "Ownable: new owner is the zero address"
